1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,377
[♪ Theme music playing]

2
00:00:24,315 --> 00:00:26,943
WOULD YOU MARRY ME?

3
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:30,673
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES,
ORGANIZATIONS, ETC. ARE FICTIONAL

4
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:32,299
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED
WITH GUARDIANS PRESENT

5
00:00:32,323 --> 00:00:34,010
ANIMALS WERE FILMED
UNDER EXPERT SUPERVISION AND WELFARE RULES

6
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:35,827
[♪ whimsical music playing]

7
00:00:38,705 --> 00:00:42,792
Last year's blue crab festival logo
put too much emphasis on the crab,

8
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:44,711
making it look
like a fish market promotion.

9
00:00:44,794 --> 00:00:46,838
I think that was a bit unfortunate.

10
00:00:47,213 --> 00:00:48,965
So, Merry Design Studio

11
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:50,050
[remote clicks]

12
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:53,595
Came up with a design
that portrays a festival

13
00:00:53,678 --> 00:00:56,181
you can enjoy
with family, friends, and dates.

14
00:00:57,015 --> 00:01:01,144
Also, the souvenirs you'll give out
to the visitors

15
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:06,357
will include the cute crab image
that we designed.

16
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:08,443
Like this.

17
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:11,352
GENERAL EVALUATION:
I DO NOT WISH TO SELECT THIS COMPANY

18
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:12,697
[sighs]

19
00:01:13,698 --> 00:01:16,785
Ms. Yoo, do you like blue crabs?

20
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:18,244
Of course, I do.

21
00:01:18,453 --> 00:01:20,830
I'm a blue crab killer.

22
00:01:20,914 --> 00:01:23,625
I can eat about three in a sitting.

23
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:28,671
Ohh! Say there's a big one
and a small one. Which would you prefer?

24
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:31,966
Of course, I prefer a big, fleshy one.

25
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:34,594
The salty, flavorful taste of a fat crab...

26
00:01:34,677 --> 00:01:37,138
My mouth is watering already.

27
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:38,890
So, you like them big.

28
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:41,017
There's more to it than just the size.

29
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:43,019
[men laughing]

30
00:01:43,103 --> 00:01:45,021
Ms. Yoo, you're not married, are you?

31
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:46,940
- No.
- Hmm.

32
00:01:47,732 --> 00:01:49,109
- [clicks tongue]
- [chuckles]

33
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:51,152
Show her what's good.

34
00:01:51,236 --> 00:01:53,863
She likes them big and fleshy.

35
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:56,699
He's known as the Hongju City Killer.

36
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:58,493
- Good luck with him.
- [men laughing]

37
00:01:58,827 --> 00:02:01,037
- Watch yourself.
- I will.

38
00:02:01,579 --> 00:02:02,681
2025 BLUE CRAB FESTIVAL
DESIGN PITCH

39
00:02:02,705 --> 00:02:04,833
Sir, what you just said.

40
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:07,127
May I ask exactly what you meant?

41
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:09,712
Pardon? What did I say?

42
00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:11,965
You wished me good luck.

43
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:13,967
Good luck with what, exactly?

44
00:02:14,050 --> 00:02:15,760
Why don't you wrap up your presentation?

45
00:02:15,844 --> 00:02:18,763
We're short on time,
so don't try to pick a fight.

46
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:20,265
I'm not picking a fight.

47
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:24,102
I just want to know
what you meant when you said

48
00:02:24,185 --> 00:02:25,937
- [man] Ms. Yoo?
- Yes?

49
00:02:26,020 --> 00:02:27,021
Don't you want the job?

50
00:02:27,772 --> 00:02:30,275
We wanted to give
an obscure company a project,

51
00:02:30,358 --> 00:02:33,069
but who'd want to work
with someone so aggressive?

52
00:02:34,279 --> 00:02:36,656
[sighs deeply]

53
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:43,997
Fine.

54
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,123
Don't work with me.

55
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,042
I refuse the job.

56
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:50,712
I'm sorry, but to be honest,

57
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:53,923
I'm picky about who I work with myself.

58
00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:56,467
I might as well say this
since I won't get the job.

59
00:02:56,551 --> 00:02:58,136
You there.

60
00:03:00,638 --> 00:03:02,932
Yes, you. The man who just pointed.

61
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:05,226
Do you think you hold a lot of power?

62
00:03:06,603 --> 00:03:09,772
You might have the advantage here,
but outside, I have the upper hand.

63
00:03:09,856 --> 00:03:12,483
My taxes pay your salary.

64
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:13,818
- [scoffs]
- [men snicker]

65
00:03:13,902 --> 00:03:15,028
I had no idea

66
00:03:15,111 --> 00:03:18,615
my tax money ended up
in the pockets of such trash.

67
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:20,301
- [stutters] What?
- [♪ dramatic music playing]

68
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:22,076
What did you just say?

69
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,703
- Me?
- Yes, you.

70
00:03:23,786 --> 00:03:26,080
- How old are you?
- Why would you ask my age?

71
00:03:26,164 --> 00:03:29,167
- How dare she talk like that?
- Are you jealous that I'm young?

72
00:03:29,709 --> 00:03:31,502
You dare take that tone with me?

73
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:33,421
- Let go of me.
- [man] Leave it.

74
00:03:33,504 --> 00:03:37,175
- Do you look down on our city?
- No, Hongju City is blameless.

75
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,637
JAMYANG PRINT SHOP

76
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:48,811
[woman over phone] So basically,
you caused a stir and got kicked out.

77
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,104
Don't worry.

78
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:51,314
You're my only employee.

79
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:53,024
I'll manage to pay you somehow.

80
00:03:53,107 --> 00:03:54,359
[woman] I doubt that.

81
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:57,612
We scored zero projects this month.

82
00:03:57,695 --> 00:03:59,489
How will you pay this month's rent?

83
00:04:00,156 --> 00:04:02,617
Did we get any inquiries
on our social platforms?

84
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:06,412
Stay on the line while I go and see.

85
00:04:09,707 --> 00:04:12,377
I think we got a couple of small jobs.

86
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:14,420
2 PROJECTS UNDERWAY.

87
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:16,631
Giveaways for a new butcher shop

88
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:18,383
and a logo for a Magok coffee shop.

89
00:04:18,466 --> 00:04:21,928
The coffee shop owner wants to see
a portfolio before they decide.

90
00:04:22,011 --> 00:04:24,305
Should we send our old herbal tea design?

91
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:26,641
Sure, will you come back to the office?

92
00:04:26,724 --> 00:04:28,059
Oh, no. I have to drop by

93
00:04:28,142 --> 00:04:30,645
a nearby department store
while I'm out in Euljiro.

94
00:04:30,728 --> 00:04:32,939
You can finish the draft and go home.

95
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:37,193
[line disconnects]

96
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:38,403
Sir.

97
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:43,616
Could you lower
the saturation of this part

98
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,576
while keeping the color Pantone 213?

99
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:46,661
I lowered it already.

100
00:04:46,744 --> 00:04:50,623
Yes, but the case is transparent,
so it'll look different when it's filled.

101
00:04:50,707 --> 00:04:52,667
You can't mind that, too. Who will notice?

102
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:54,335
A reprint will just cost you more.

103
00:04:54,419 --> 00:04:55,920
I know the difference.

104
00:04:56,004 --> 00:04:59,257
I can't sell anything to a customer
if something bothers me.

105
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:00,341
You're too picky.

106
00:05:00,633 --> 00:05:02,193
You'll never make a fortune doing that.

107
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:04,679
Sir.

108
00:05:05,054 --> 00:05:06,055
Thank you.

109
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:08,308
[giggles]

110
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:13,706
[♪ Orchestral music playing in store]

111
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:16,566
We engraved the wedding bands
with your initials.

112
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:18,318
Thanks.

113
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:21,529
The receipt, warranty card,
and raffle ticket are inside.

114
00:05:21,612 --> 00:05:23,156
Thank you.

115
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:24,907
Thank you. Goodbye.

116
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:31,205
I emailed a copy
of my boyfriend's passport.

117
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:32,874
Yes, Kim Wooju.

118
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:35,126
Thank you. Bye.

119
00:05:37,211 --> 00:05:40,548
That's the honeymoon booked.

120
00:05:43,051 --> 00:05:45,011
WHEN WILL YOU BE DONE?

121
00:05:45,094 --> 00:05:46,554
[♪ Enthralling music playing]

122
00:05:46,637 --> 00:05:47,889
[both breathing heavily]

123
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:53,269
I love you.

124
00:05:57,857 --> 00:05:59,108
[breathing heavily]

125
00:06:04,781 --> 00:06:06,449
[moaning]

126
00:06:07,909 --> 00:06:09,577
- [phone vibrates]
- [chuckles softly]

127
00:06:12,413 --> 00:06:13,748
[Ms. Yoo] When will you be done?

128
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:16,751
[Wooju] I'm in a meeting.

129
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:18,723
[Ms. Yoo] You're working late again today?

130
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:19,855
YOU'RE WORKING LATE AGAIN TODAY?

131
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:20,880
It must be tiresome.

132
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:22,066
- Who is it?
- [Ms. Yoo] You've got this.

133
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,690
- [Wooju] I love you.
- What did she say?

134
00:06:29,931 --> 00:06:31,474
[both breathing heavily]

135
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:35,228
[Ms. Yoo] I was hoping to have dinner
with him.

136
00:06:35,311 --> 00:06:36,354
Oh, gosh.

137
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:37,605
Sorry.

138
00:06:40,149 --> 00:06:41,776
[♪ Pleasant whimsical music playing]

139
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:43,069
WOULD YOU MARRY ME?

140
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:45,238
EPISODE 1.

141
00:06:49,283 --> 00:06:50,660
ALWAYS ACCEPT AN APOLOGY.

142
00:06:50,743 --> 00:06:52,638
CUTE WOOJU
NEVER LET A FIGHT LAST MORE THAN A DAY.

143
00:06:52,662 --> 00:06:54,038
WOOJU TAKES OUT THE RECYCLING.

144
00:06:54,122 --> 00:06:55,623
HANDWRITE LETTERS ON ANNIVERSARIES.

145
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:57,041
TAKE A MONTHLY TRIP IN KOREA.

146
00:06:57,625 --> 00:06:59,710
Forget the wedding and whatnot.

147
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:01,170
I wish I could call it all off.

148
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:04,590
Oh, Meri.

149
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:08,970
You can't just register your marriage
and say it's done.

150
00:07:09,053 --> 00:07:11,681
- It's a hassle, but a necessary one.
- [Meri] Mom.

151
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:14,350
The problem is that there's so much to do.

152
00:07:14,434 --> 00:07:16,060
I have so little money to spare,

153
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:18,729
but Wooju's mother
keeps going on about a hotel.

154
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,606
It's driving me up the wall.

155
00:07:21,315 --> 00:07:24,402
If she has the money for a hotel wedding,
she should contribute to our rent.

156
00:07:24,485 --> 00:07:27,947
Her son has a fancy degree,
and her husband's a university professor.

157
00:07:28,364 --> 00:07:30,533
She has an appearance to keep up.

158
00:07:30,616 --> 00:07:32,368
Try to understand. [Chuckles]

159
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:34,078
Where are you?

160
00:07:34,162 --> 00:07:35,538
- Did you have dinner?
- Yes.

161
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:37,165
I ate.

162
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,876
I'm at our new place.

163
00:07:40,626 --> 00:07:43,713
I come by whenever I can
to unpack and organize stuff.

164
00:07:45,173 --> 00:07:47,842
Did you have dinner, Mom?

165
00:07:47,925 --> 00:07:49,802
I did. What about Wooju?

166
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:52,305
He moved in already.

167
00:07:53,806 --> 00:07:56,100
He didn't call to tell you?

168
00:07:57,185 --> 00:08:00,229
He must know we couldn't afford this place
without your help.

169
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:01,898
Leave it.

170
00:08:01,981 --> 00:08:04,484
I gave you the money
so he'd be good to you.

171
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:08,070
Let me give you a word of caution.

172
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:10,990
Don't nag him for not having
contributed to the deposit.

173
00:08:11,073 --> 00:08:13,117
You shouldn't discourage a man.

174
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:15,286
What? Why would he be discouraged?

175
00:08:15,369 --> 00:08:17,121
I cater to him in every way.

176
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:20,374
I'm good wife material
that's rare these days.

177
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:21,959
You're the kid out of the two of us.

178
00:08:22,043 --> 00:08:23,419
[chuckling]

179
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:25,505
Mom.

180
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:28,341
I'll make lots of money

181
00:08:28,424 --> 00:08:30,468
and pay you back soo... [gasps]

182
00:08:31,135 --> 00:08:32,845
What's the matter?

183
00:08:33,554 --> 00:08:34,680
It's fine.

184
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:36,682
I just stepped on something.

185
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:42,980
Mom, I'll call you back a bit later.

186
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:44,941
Bye.

187
00:08:55,076 --> 00:08:56,452
What is this?

188
00:08:57,286 --> 00:08:58,663
It's not my...

189
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:01,499
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

190
00:09:14,845 --> 00:09:16,430
[♪ Suspenseful music swells]

191
00:09:30,194 --> 00:09:31,237
[music stops]

192
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:34,490
[♪ Pop music playing in background]

193
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:38,786
[chuckling] I look like a model.

194
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:44,333
What about this?

195
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,669
It's when I played golf
with some investors.

196
00:09:47,336 --> 00:09:48,337
I know that.

197
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:50,590
- A comment on that post.
- Yes.

198
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:53,092
"Sweet Jenny 97."

199
00:09:53,175 --> 00:09:54,215
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

200
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:57,305
- What?
- She liked every single post of yours.

201
00:09:57,847 --> 00:09:59,932
SWEET_JENNY97
YOUR FACE IS ALL I SEE.

202
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:02,476
You follow each other. Who is that?

203
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:04,937
[chuckles]

204
00:10:05,021 --> 00:10:06,772
She's just a colleague of mine.

205
00:10:07,398 --> 00:10:09,400
Didn't I mention her? I bet I did.
[clears throat]

206
00:10:09,483 --> 00:10:12,153
She went to school in Hong Kong.

207
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:13,362
Did you sleep with her?

208
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:15,615
[coughs]

209
00:10:17,575 --> 00:10:18,993
[chuckles nervously] Hey.

210
00:10:19,076 --> 00:10:20,119
What's up with you?

211
00:10:20,202 --> 00:10:22,872
Why the heck would I sleep with her?

212
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:24,206
[sighs deeply]

213
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,168
[earring clatters]

214
00:10:27,251 --> 00:10:29,420
Then why did I find this by the bed?

215
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:31,130
What's this?

216
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:43,017
[♪ Dramatic sting]

217
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:44,894
[♪ Tense music playing]

218
00:10:49,857 --> 00:10:53,152
Oh, I was at a company workshop
in Gangwon-do last week.

219
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:55,404
A few colleagues came by to look around.

220
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:58,574
- Colleagues?
- You see, they were dead curious.

221
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:01,327
She must have dropped it then.

222
00:11:02,411 --> 00:11:04,038
I should give it back.

223
00:11:05,498 --> 00:11:09,877
Last week, your department head
went fishing on Anmyeondo Island.

224
00:11:11,587 --> 00:11:14,757
Your section chief
took his kids to Lotte World.

225
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:16,884
Assistant Manager Jang.

226
00:11:17,885 --> 00:11:20,554
He went to the wedding
of a guy he met in the army.

227
00:11:21,681 --> 00:11:23,432
The Gangwon-do workshop...

228
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:26,977
Did you and Jenny go on your own?

229
00:11:32,692 --> 00:11:33,818
Sunset Resort.

230
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:36,696
Each suite has a private pool.

231
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:40,157
You were there overnight,
so I don't need to ask what went on.

232
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:42,284
What do you think?

233
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:43,703
If you keep denying it,

234
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:47,164
should I cause a scene at your office
like some soap opera?

235
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:48,708
[spits, coughing]

236
00:11:54,922 --> 00:11:55,923
Hey.

237
00:11:56,924 --> 00:11:58,008
[sniffles]

238
00:12:01,721 --> 00:12:02,847
Fine.

239
00:12:02,930 --> 00:12:04,807
I'll come clean.

240
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:06,434
I'm Adam, who fell for a snake's lies.

241
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:08,644
I partook of the forbidden fruit. So what?

242
00:12:08,728 --> 00:12:10,563
- [café patrons murmuring]
- [♪ ominous sting]

243
00:12:10,646 --> 00:12:11,981
"So what?"

244
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:14,233
Why do you think I did?

245
00:12:15,192 --> 00:12:17,361
It was because I was under so much stress.

246
00:12:18,112 --> 00:12:20,006
My investors call every day
about profit margins,

247
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:21,950
while I'm just a newbie
with a wedding coming up.

248
00:12:22,032 --> 00:12:23,784
Don't you see how much is on my mind?

249
00:12:23,868 --> 00:12:26,662
I was already on edge,
and you nagged me so much.

250
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:29,290
You called, texted, and bossed me about
with the wedding prep.

251
00:12:29,373 --> 00:12:30,851
[laughing] I felt like I was being fried.

252
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:33,002
Am I getting married on my own? [Echoes]

253
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:35,212
I work full-time, too.

254
00:12:35,379 --> 00:12:37,673
- I'm busy, too!
- I know you are!

255
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:39,008
That's why I... [echoes]

256
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:41,510
[sighs]

257
00:12:42,219 --> 00:12:43,304
I'm sorry.

258
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:44,448
[♪ Dramatic guitar music playing]

259
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:45,765
I'm a jerk.

260
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:46,849
[café patrons gasp]

261
00:12:46,932 --> 00:12:48,017
I deserve a beating!

262
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:51,061
Say a number. How many slaps?

263
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:52,730
[sighs]

264
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:54,774
I know you have a glib tongue.

265
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:57,443
But not today.

266
00:12:59,069 --> 00:13:00,696
I won't let you off like that today.

267
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:07,912
Meri. Let's think rationally.

268
00:13:08,579 --> 00:13:10,474
We booked a wedding hall,
got a marriage license,

269
00:13:10,498 --> 00:13:11,540
and rented an apartment.

270
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:13,727
Leave me, and you'll be a divorcée
even without a wedding.

271
00:13:13,751 --> 00:13:15,461
Wow, isn't that so unfair?

272
00:13:15,544 --> 00:13:16,545
It is unfair!

273
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:18,380
Right? That makes zero sense.

274
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:20,674
That girl, Jenny...

275
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:22,968
She's just a fling.

276
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:33,479
And you and I will be together forever.

277
00:13:34,188 --> 00:13:35,815
It was a one-time mistake,

278
00:13:36,106 --> 00:13:37,691
and I ended it with her already.

279
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:40,861
[sighs wearily]

280
00:13:42,071 --> 00:13:43,405
[phone vibrates]

281
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:47,368
JENNY

282
00:13:47,451 --> 00:13:48,762
[Jenny] When are you coming over?

283
00:13:48,786 --> 00:13:51,163
I'm waiting for you in the underwear
you got me yesterday.

284
00:13:51,247 --> 00:13:52,248
Isn't it pretty?

285
00:13:52,331 --> 00:13:54,834
[♪ Dramatic sting]

286
00:13:57,169 --> 00:13:58,212
[clears throat]

287
00:13:58,295 --> 00:14:00,172
[♪ Tense music playing]

288
00:14:01,340 --> 00:14:02,591
It's my section chief.

289
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:04,009
About tomorrow's business trip.

290
00:14:05,261 --> 00:14:07,680
Did I ever ask to see your phone?

291
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:10,599
No.

292
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:12,476
I have a bad feeling.

293
00:14:13,227 --> 00:14:16,188
If I don't see this now,
I might doubt you forever and ever.

294
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:17,690
Move your hand.

295
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:29,577
What are you doing?

296
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:31,120
It was my section chief.

297
00:14:31,203 --> 00:14:32,454
Let me see it.

298
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:33,598
It was my section chief, okay?

299
00:14:33,622 --> 00:14:35,165
Exactly, that's why I want to see.

300
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:36,409
Why see my section chief's...

301
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:41,088
[screams]

302
00:14:42,214 --> 00:14:43,299
Are you all right?

303
00:14:43,382 --> 00:14:44,609
- Did he step on her hand?
- Hey.

304
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:45,634
He stomped on her hand.

305
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:47,428
- What's going on?
- Is she okay?

306
00:14:49,179 --> 00:14:51,473
[Wooju] Why did you try to see my phone?

307
00:14:52,182 --> 00:14:54,702
You shouldn't cross the line
however close you are with someone.

308
00:14:56,687 --> 00:14:57,771
Let's see your hand.

309
00:14:58,647 --> 00:14:59,899
[breathing heavily]

310
00:15:00,816 --> 00:15:01,817
"The line?"

311
00:15:03,777 --> 00:15:05,571
You're the one who crossed the line.

312
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:08,782
That apartment is ours,
and we're soon to be married.

313
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:11,243
You brought another woman over.

314
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:12,661
[café patrons gasp]

315
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:14,330
- No way.
- How could you do that?

316
00:15:14,997 --> 00:15:16,516
[café patron 1] Is he out of his mind?

317
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:17,750
[café patrons murmuring]

318
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:20,920
[♪ Melancholy music playing]

319
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:23,881
[voice shaking] For seven months
after you got your new job,

320
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:27,092
you always worked late
or had a team dinner.

321
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:29,345
You were so hard to reach.

322
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:34,224
You even forgot my birthday
and our anniversary.

323
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:38,196
I got fitted for a wedding dress on my own
because you were too busy.

324
00:15:40,689 --> 00:15:41,690
I couldn't bear

325
00:15:44,735 --> 00:15:47,321
the thought of letting
our five years go to waste.

326
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:52,409
So, I told myself to ignore everything
and just marry you.

327
00:15:54,119 --> 00:15:55,245
But I won't.

328
00:15:56,705 --> 00:15:59,416
I think I'll divorce you one day
even if we do get married.

329
00:16:01,543 --> 00:16:02,962
If it's bound to happen one day,

330
00:16:04,463 --> 00:16:05,756
that might as well be today.

331
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:09,718
Meri.

332
00:16:17,518 --> 00:16:19,103
[café patrons gasp]

333
00:16:19,186 --> 00:16:20,506
[♪ Dramatic guitar music playing]

334
00:16:21,438 --> 00:16:23,118
[café patron 2] She actually drenched him.

335
00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:26,075
- [café patron 3] Did you see that?
- [café patron 4] That was insane.

336
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:35,703
[passenger] She's pretty old, you see,
and I need to sit next to her.

337
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:38,056
- [air hostess] Is it for health concerns?
- [passenger] Yes.

338
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,915
Could you get him to swap with me?

339
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:42,167
[air hostess] I'll ask the gentleman
for you.

340
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:43,971
- Will you come with me?
- [passenger] Sure.

341
00:16:44,461 --> 00:16:46,501
- [air hostess] Let's go.
- [passenger] Yes, thanks.

342
00:16:50,134 --> 00:16:51,427
[air hostess] Sir?

343
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:53,429
Were you assigned seat 5D?

344
00:16:54,096 --> 00:16:55,139
Yes.

345
00:16:55,222 --> 00:16:56,682
This gentleman says

346
00:16:56,765 --> 00:17:00,227
he was given a seat
apart from his elderly mother.

347
00:17:00,310 --> 00:17:02,229
He'd like to know
if you could switch with him.

348
00:17:02,730 --> 00:17:04,189
I'm so sorry.

349
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:06,066
My mother is very old,

350
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:09,028
and I need to assist her during the flight.

351
00:17:09,987 --> 00:17:11,530
Will you swap with me, sir?

352
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:13,198
I don't want to.

353
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:16,410
My seat is also in business class.

354
00:17:16,493 --> 00:17:18,162
[♪ Upbeat music playing]

355
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:19,913
Sir?

356
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:23,459
Hello?

357
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:34,636
[air hostess over PA system]
We have reached our destination

358
00:17:34,803 --> 00:17:36,930
at Incheon International Airport.

359
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:40,309
When opening overhead storage
after the plane stops,

360
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:42,936
please take care to ensure
nothing falls out.

361
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:44,021
Thank you.

362
00:17:47,691 --> 00:17:50,611
14 HOURS PRIOR.

363
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:54,323
The old hag's trying to run away
without selling the land,

364
00:17:54,782 --> 00:17:57,826
so I'll sit next to her
and get her to sign the papers.

365
00:17:59,161 --> 00:18:01,997
My big sister in Seoul
won't let me anywhere near Mom.

366
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:05,584
I need to get the papers signed
on the plane.

367
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:07,419
Mom could die any day now.

368
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:09,713
That's why I need the papers signed soon.

369
00:18:11,548 --> 00:18:12,633
Ma'am.

370
00:18:13,509 --> 00:18:16,261
Keep the land deeds until the day you die.

371
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:18,388
Don't trust your son
and hand it right over.

372
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:20,474
You can't trust anyone out there.

373
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:33,862
[grunts]

374
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:36,115
I just landed.

375
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:37,438
I'm going straight to Yangyang.

376
00:18:38,408 --> 00:18:39,808
[woman over phone] You rotten fool.

377
00:18:39,868 --> 00:18:41,495
Why not drop by to say hi first?

378
00:18:42,287 --> 00:18:44,540
I made a video call
before I got on the plane.

379
00:18:44,623 --> 00:18:46,500
It's not that I want to see you.

380
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,335
I picked too many zucchinis.

381
00:18:48,418 --> 00:18:49,795
I can't eat it all.

382
00:18:49,878 --> 00:18:53,882
Put them in the freezer.
I'll eat them when I'm back.

383
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:56,468
You never say you'll come by.

384
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:59,972
I'm scared you'll put me right to work.

385
00:19:00,055 --> 00:19:02,432
Grandma, it's my first holiday
in three years.

386
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:04,810
I'll let you off just this once.

387
00:19:04,893 --> 00:19:06,520
Just wait until you start work.

388
00:19:06,603 --> 00:19:09,648
How can you only think about putting
your one and only grandson to work?

389
00:19:09,731 --> 00:19:11,984
I spent a fortune to feed and educate you.

390
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:14,420
I have a long way to go
to make up for the tuition I invested.

391
00:19:14,444 --> 00:19:16,155
You're so calculative.

392
00:19:16,238 --> 00:19:18,490
A peddler's not a peddler
if they're not calculative.

393
00:19:18,574 --> 00:19:19,783
Okay, fine.

394
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:23,495
Good luck with the zucchinis
and sweet potatoes while I'm away.

395
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:24,621
See you in a month.

396
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:27,749
I'll be in touch.

397
00:19:29,751 --> 00:19:30,961
[chuckles]

398
00:19:38,969 --> 00:19:40,846
You prepared a lot of food.

399
00:19:40,929 --> 00:19:43,849
- Shall I stay and eat with you?
- No.

400
00:19:44,641 --> 00:19:47,978
He survived on hamburgers
in a foreign country without his parents.

401
00:19:48,061 --> 00:19:50,439
I was hoping to feed him
some home-cooked food.

402
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:52,691
[♪ Upbeat pop music
playing over car stereo]

403
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:33,649
[sighs in relief]

404
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,699
[♪ Gentle synth music playing]

405
00:20:49,581 --> 00:20:51,375
[♪ Upbeat pop music playing]

406
00:21:03,053 --> 00:21:04,137
[cat meows]

407
00:21:06,974 --> 00:21:08,058
[meows]

408
00:21:10,227 --> 00:21:11,436
[purrs]

409
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:13,563
[sighs]

410
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:33,709
HAPPINESS

411
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:46,638
[gasps]

412
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:48,640
[exclaims excitedly]

413
00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:56,898
ONE MONTH LATER

414
00:21:56,982 --> 00:21:59,062
[judge] The one-month consideration period
has ended,

415
00:21:59,359 --> 00:22:04,072
and I confirm Kim Wooju
and Yoo Meri's intent to divorce.

416
00:22:04,614 --> 00:22:05,657
[Meri sighs softly]

417
00:22:10,245 --> 00:22:12,581
I can't believe
all the things you make me do.

418
00:22:13,081 --> 00:22:14,875
Stupid me.

419
00:22:14,958 --> 00:22:17,544
I shouldn't have registered our marriage
when you asked to.

420
00:22:17,627 --> 00:22:19,939
It was the only way to get your mother
to pay the housing deposit.

421
00:22:19,963 --> 00:22:21,774
Are you saying
she forced you against your will?

422
00:22:21,798 --> 00:22:23,216
- You...
- That's not true.

423
00:22:24,801 --> 00:22:25,927
[sighs deeply]

424
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:31,558
- What did your mother say?
- She didn't say anything.

425
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:35,145
I couldn't tell her I became a divorcée
before I even walked down the aisle.

426
00:22:36,104 --> 00:22:37,356
Sorry.

427
00:22:38,523 --> 00:22:40,203
I'll tell her later when the time's right.

428
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:42,778
I said we'd postpone the wedding
because you're busy.

429
00:22:42,861 --> 00:22:44,154
Keep that in mind.

430
00:22:45,280 --> 00:22:46,281
Okay.

431
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:49,951
I'll vacate the apartment,
so take your stuff.

432
00:22:50,952 --> 00:22:52,162
Are you moving out?

433
00:22:52,245 --> 00:22:53,872
Do you want me to live there when you

434
00:22:53,955 --> 00:22:55,707
I took out a massive loan.

435
00:22:56,458 --> 00:22:57,459
You're right.

436
00:22:58,460 --> 00:22:59,461
[chuckles softly]

437
00:22:59,544 --> 00:23:01,129
You'll have much less debt, at least.

438
00:23:01,296 --> 00:23:02,714
It's a good thing we broke up.

439
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:04,925
Sure, it's just great.

440
00:23:05,008 --> 00:23:06,802
I'm so grateful I could cry.

441
00:23:06,885 --> 00:23:08,095
I have much less debt.

442
00:23:09,137 --> 00:23:10,389
[phone vibrating]

443
00:23:17,562 --> 00:23:18,563
[whispering] Hi, Jenny.

444
00:23:20,273 --> 00:23:21,525
Are you at the airport already?

445
00:23:22,109 --> 00:23:23,652
Yes, I'm just about to leave.

446
00:23:24,361 --> 00:23:25,362
Okay, see you soon.

447
00:23:26,405 --> 00:23:27,531
[line disconnects]

448
00:23:30,951 --> 00:23:32,871
[in normal voice]
I'm going somewhere on holiday.

449
00:23:33,870 --> 00:23:35,497
I have to hand in our divorce decree.

450
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:36,740
Did you fill in your details?

451
00:23:37,916 --> 00:23:39,126
Yes.

452
00:23:39,209 --> 00:23:40,544
Thanks for submitting it for me.

453
00:23:41,002 --> 00:23:42,254
Don't thank me.

454
00:23:42,337 --> 00:23:43,588
I'm doing it in case you don't.

455
00:23:46,007 --> 00:23:48,343
Hey, don't hate me too much.

456
00:23:49,177 --> 00:23:50,178
We were

457
00:23:51,721 --> 00:23:53,181
in love for a while.

458
00:23:56,852 --> 00:23:57,853
[Wooju sighs wistfully]

459
00:23:59,438 --> 00:24:00,439
Meri.

460
00:24:00,772 --> 00:24:01,857
Live a good life.

461
00:24:01,940 --> 00:24:02,983
Forget all about me.

462
00:24:06,278 --> 00:24:07,320
Wooju.

463
00:24:08,155 --> 00:24:09,156
Get lost.

464
00:24:09,239 --> 00:24:10,866
[♪ Dramatic guitar music playing]

465
00:24:11,408 --> 00:24:13,743
Hey, you should find a good guy.

466
00:24:13,827 --> 00:24:15,454
Don't wait too long.

467
00:24:15,537 --> 00:24:18,206
You get over love with love!

468
00:24:23,420 --> 00:24:24,754
I'm on my way now.

469
00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:30,177
Darn you!

470
00:24:31,928 --> 00:24:33,180
[sighs in exasperation]

471
00:24:39,644 --> 00:24:43,523
HOME APPLIANCE FAIR FOR NEWLYWEDS.

472
00:24:43,607 --> 00:24:45,484
SEOUL FAMILY COURT

473
00:24:49,654 --> 00:24:50,864
[phone vibrates]

474
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:57,579
RIZZ WEDDING HALL

475
00:24:57,662 --> 00:25:01,374
THE BLUEMON HALL RESERVATION WAS CANCELED

476
00:25:01,458 --> 00:25:02,459
[phone vibrates]

477
00:25:02,542 --> 00:25:05,462
DREAM TRAVEL AGENTS

478
00:25:05,545 --> 00:25:08,632
YOUR HONEYMOON PACKAGE WAS CANCELED

479
00:25:08,715 --> 00:25:09,925
[phone vibrates]

480
00:25:10,675 --> 00:25:14,054
ELLE WEDDING DRESSES
YOUR WEDDING DRESS RENTAL WAS CANCELED

481
00:25:30,529 --> 00:25:32,864
[distorted laughter]

482
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:42,582
[Meri] Do clean breakups exist?

483
00:25:43,291 --> 00:25:44,918
[♪ Slow melancholy music playing]

484
00:25:45,001 --> 00:25:46,294
[Meri sighs]

485
00:25:57,097 --> 00:25:59,099
You pretend to be okay.

486
00:26:00,433 --> 00:26:02,227
What's broken

487
00:26:03,395 --> 00:26:05,397
can't be glued back together.

488
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:27,377
- [Wooju] Meri.
- Yes?

489
00:26:28,336 --> 00:26:30,213
- I love you.
- I love you, too.

490
00:26:35,218 --> 00:26:36,344
[giggles]

491
00:26:43,476 --> 00:26:44,811
[inhales sharply]

492
00:26:44,894 --> 00:26:46,813
I'll live well without you now.

493
00:26:55,447 --> 00:26:57,240
I'll make lots of money.

494
00:27:00,410 --> 00:27:02,912
I'll go on lots of trips.

495
00:27:05,123 --> 00:27:06,875
I'll even go on blind dates.

496
00:27:10,837 --> 00:27:12,677
[voice shaking] I'll forget the likes of you.

497
00:27:17,886 --> 00:27:19,012
I'll live.

498
00:27:23,266 --> 00:27:24,434
I'll.

499
00:27:27,187 --> 00:27:28,396
I'll be really busy.

500
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:35,403
[sobbing]

501
00:27:42,243 --> 00:27:43,620
[continues sobbing]

502
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:02,889
Young man.

503
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:05,558
I'd grown to like you.

504
00:28:05,642 --> 00:28:06,810
I'm sad to see you go.

505
00:28:07,852 --> 00:28:10,063
They say those who meet must part.

506
00:28:10,146 --> 00:28:11,147
Here.

507
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:13,358
- Eat it on the way.
- What's this?

508
00:28:14,859 --> 00:28:16,069
Ooh!

509
00:28:16,152 --> 00:28:17,153
It's corn bread.

510
00:28:17,237 --> 00:28:19,197
I got it from the best place nearby.

511
00:28:19,781 --> 00:28:20,865
Just for you.

512
00:28:21,908 --> 00:28:22,909
How is it?

513
00:28:23,410 --> 00:28:25,370
- It's good.
- [chuckles]

514
00:28:25,954 --> 00:28:28,081
I should bring you some bread next time.

515
00:28:28,373 --> 00:28:29,374
Bread?

516
00:28:29,457 --> 00:28:33,294
My family owns the best bakery
in the whole country.

517
00:28:33,378 --> 00:28:34,421
A bakery?

518
00:28:34,504 --> 00:28:36,339
- Hmm.
- Oh! [Chuckles]

519
00:28:36,423 --> 00:28:37,465
Thanks for this.

520
00:28:37,549 --> 00:28:39,718
MYUNGSOONDANG

521
00:28:40,552 --> 00:28:41,761
[interviewer] Congratulations.

522
00:28:41,845 --> 00:28:46,641
Myungsoondang won the President's Award
at the Industrial Day award ceremony.

523
00:28:46,725 --> 00:28:48,518
How do you feel?

524
00:28:49,436 --> 00:28:51,020
[interviewee] I don't have much to say,

525
00:28:51,104 --> 00:28:53,273
but that I'm grateful and thankful.
[chuckles]

526
00:28:53,982 --> 00:28:55,835
I appreciate the acknowledgement
that I make everything

527
00:28:55,859 --> 00:28:58,820
as if it were for my own child,
using no preservatives.

528
00:28:58,903 --> 00:29:00,572
I can only thank you.

529
00:29:00,655 --> 00:29:02,240
[interviewer] How humble of you.

530
00:29:02,323 --> 00:29:05,034
Myungsoondang is Korea's first-ever bakery

531
00:29:05,118 --> 00:29:06,262
- as well as...
- Your grandma

532
00:29:06,286 --> 00:29:09,789
dumps a whole load of additives
when she cooks.

533
00:29:10,206 --> 00:29:12,333
- Just not in the bread.
- [camera shutter clicking]

534
00:29:12,417 --> 00:29:14,961
You should, too,
since your food is horrible.

535
00:29:15,044 --> 00:29:17,213
[interviewer] ...you even announced
a new beginning.

536
00:29:17,297 --> 00:29:19,233
- Eat all you want.
- [interviewer] How is that going?

537
00:29:19,257 --> 00:29:22,635
At the Paris Dessert Fair last year,

538
00:29:22,719 --> 00:29:24,971
our hangwa was incredibly popular.

539
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,891
I got many inquiries
from department stores

540
00:29:27,974 --> 00:29:30,059
in Paris, London, and New York,

541
00:29:30,143 --> 00:29:33,313
so I plan to promote
our traditional hangwa

542
00:29:33,396 --> 00:29:35,774
as a K-dessert throughout the world.

543
00:29:35,857 --> 00:29:36,941
KOREA ECONOMY

544
00:29:37,025 --> 00:29:38,568
[♪ feel-good music playing]

545
00:29:40,069 --> 00:29:43,198
Chairwoman, can you pose
with one of your products this time?

546
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:44,365
Yes, sure.

547
00:29:45,533 --> 00:29:46,576
Here you go, Chairwoman.

548
00:29:46,659 --> 00:29:47,994
Get me one of our new products.

549
00:29:48,077 --> 00:29:49,078
Here it is.

550
00:29:53,249 --> 00:29:56,628
Will you take the photo
so the hangwa looks nicer than me?

551
00:29:56,711 --> 00:29:59,214
Mom, you're not shooting a commercial.

552
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:02,425
Why not make an interview
work as well as one?

553
00:30:02,509 --> 00:30:04,385
Yes, let's milk it for all it's worth.

554
00:30:05,303 --> 00:30:06,513
"Make it worthwhile."

555
00:30:06,596 --> 00:30:07,680
Use nice language.

556
00:30:07,764 --> 00:30:09,057
I used easy language, Mom.

557
00:30:09,140 --> 00:30:10,141
[snarls]

558
00:30:10,225 --> 00:30:11,351
[giggling]

559
00:30:11,935 --> 00:30:13,645
[photographer] One, two, three.

560
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:15,909
CHAIRWOMAN KO
WINS ANNUAL PRESIDENT'S AWARD

561
00:30:20,276 --> 00:30:21,319
[slurps]

562
00:30:21,653 --> 00:30:23,404
What did the coffee shop owner say?

563
00:30:25,073 --> 00:30:26,074
Really?

564
00:30:26,449 --> 00:30:27,909
We'll go with a cat, then.

565
00:30:27,992 --> 00:30:28,993
The customer is king.

566
00:30:30,203 --> 00:30:32,372
Let's put just the shop name
on the napkins

567
00:30:32,455 --> 00:30:34,916
and put stickers
on the paper cups and sleeves.

568
00:30:35,917 --> 00:30:37,418
Are the samples at the office?

569
00:30:39,128 --> 00:30:41,214
[gasps] Oh, yes. I brought them home.

570
00:30:43,424 --> 00:30:45,426
The samples...

571
00:30:49,597 --> 00:30:50,598
Where did I put them?

572
00:30:53,393 --> 00:30:54,477
Here they are.

573
00:30:59,649 --> 00:31:01,067
SEOUL FAMILY COURT

574
00:31:02,527 --> 00:31:04,195
I have to hand in our divorce decree.

575
00:31:04,279 --> 00:31:05,488
Did you fill in your details?

576
00:31:06,072 --> 00:31:07,615
I need to hand this in soon.

577
00:31:11,286 --> 00:31:12,662
[knocking at door]

578
00:31:12,745 --> 00:31:13,955
[man] Is anyone home?

579
00:31:15,081 --> 00:31:16,207
[knocking continues]

580
00:31:16,291 --> 00:31:17,625
Is someone in?

581
00:31:18,918 --> 00:31:19,919
POLICE

582
00:31:20,003 --> 00:31:21,921
Do you live here?

583
00:31:22,005 --> 00:31:23,381
Yes, is something wrong?

584
00:31:24,549 --> 00:31:25,675
[sighs in relief]

585
00:31:26,217 --> 00:31:27,635
We meet at last.

586
00:31:27,719 --> 00:31:29,178
JUNGMUN POLICE, SERVING WITH WARMTH

587
00:31:29,262 --> 00:31:30,722
[Meri] A rental con?

588
00:31:31,180 --> 00:31:33,349
[officer] The homeowner had left a realtor

589
00:31:33,433 --> 00:31:35,685
in charge of the property
while she was abroad.

590
00:31:35,768 --> 00:31:37,186
Without the realtor knowing,

591
00:31:37,270 --> 00:31:39,415
their assistant got someone
to pretend to be the homeowner

592
00:31:39,439 --> 00:31:40,899
and sign a fake lease with you.

593
00:31:40,982 --> 00:31:43,568
What happens to me, then?

594
00:31:43,651 --> 00:31:45,236
You have to move out,

595
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:47,739
or the homeowner
will report you for trespassing.

596
00:31:47,822 --> 00:31:51,075
I can't move out
until I get my security deposit back.

597
00:31:51,910 --> 00:31:55,455
You need to sue the people
who conned you to get that back.

598
00:31:56,915 --> 00:31:57,957
[sighs]

599
00:31:58,041 --> 00:32:01,628
But the fake homeowner is a vagrant
who let the scammer use his identity.

600
00:32:02,211 --> 00:32:04,714
Are you saying
I might not get my money back?

601
00:32:05,715 --> 00:32:07,133
[breathing heavily]

602
00:32:11,638 --> 00:32:12,764
WOOJU

603
00:32:12,889 --> 00:32:13,890
[line ringing]

604
00:32:17,393 --> 00:32:19,312
What? A rental con?

605
00:32:21,856 --> 00:32:23,691
You should've looked into it better.

606
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,110
Do you have rental insurance?

607
00:32:26,986 --> 00:32:29,364
Why didn't you do something that basic?

608
00:32:30,990 --> 00:32:32,075
My uncle?

609
00:32:33,076 --> 00:32:34,636
Yes, he's at the Public Prosecutors'

610
00:32:36,037 --> 00:32:38,414
I can't ask a favor for something like that.

611
00:32:38,998 --> 00:32:42,669
Don't talk as if it has
nothing to do with you. [sighs]

612
00:32:43,544 --> 00:32:46,923
I don't know anyone else to ask for help.

613
00:32:47,006 --> 00:32:48,633
Is there nothing you can do?

614
00:32:49,509 --> 00:32:52,720
My savings, a bank loan,
and my mom's money went into it.

615
00:32:52,804 --> 00:32:55,390
- It's 300 million won.
- [clears throat]

616
00:32:56,015 --> 00:32:57,016
Meri.

617
00:32:57,558 --> 00:32:58,953
It does have nothing to do with me.

618
00:32:58,977 --> 00:33:00,395
It's none of my business now.

619
00:33:00,478 --> 00:33:01,938
We're complete strangers now.

620
00:33:02,647 --> 00:33:04,691
You need to accept reality.

621
00:33:04,774 --> 00:33:06,818
Will you call me
whenever something goes wrong?

622
00:33:07,777 --> 00:33:11,072
It's really rude to call your ex
out of the blue like this.

623
00:33:11,656 --> 00:33:15,868
I picked up this time for old time's sake,
but I won't anymore, okay?

624
00:33:15,952 --> 00:33:16,953
No, wait.

625
00:33:17,912 --> 00:33:19,312
- Wooju, hello?
- [line disconnects]

626
00:33:20,206 --> 00:33:21,582
WOOJU

627
00:33:25,044 --> 00:33:28,214
[automated voice] The phone is off.
Transferring to voicemail.

628
00:33:28,297 --> 00:33:29,632
Oh, no.

629
00:33:31,718 --> 00:33:34,095
What do I do?

630
00:33:39,767 --> 00:33:41,060
He's right.

631
00:33:42,395 --> 00:33:44,856
[breathes deeply]

632
00:33:44,939 --> 00:33:46,899
We are complete strangers now.

633
00:33:48,776 --> 00:33:49,861
But even so.

634
00:33:50,403 --> 00:33:52,405
We only just broke up.

635
00:33:53,364 --> 00:33:55,033
Is that all he could say?

636
00:33:56,951 --> 00:33:59,662
I haven't even submitted
our divorce decree.

637
00:34:00,329 --> 00:34:02,081
[♪ Slow melancholy music playing]

638
00:34:13,384 --> 00:34:14,385
If not for you,

639
00:34:15,553 --> 00:34:18,389
I wouldn't even have
rented that apartment. [Sighs]

640
00:34:18,473 --> 00:34:20,850
And now you're turning your back on me?

641
00:34:21,684 --> 00:34:23,394
What am I to do now?

642
00:34:27,690 --> 00:34:29,108
[sighs]

643
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:33,571
MOM

644
00:34:34,489 --> 00:34:35,948
[phone vibrating]

645
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:43,748
Hi, Mom.

646
00:34:43,831 --> 00:34:45,708
Hey, Meri.

647
00:34:45,792 --> 00:34:48,586
I braised some yellow croaker
and seasoned some cucumbers.

648
00:34:48,669 --> 00:34:50,064
Wooju's parents haven't moved, right?

649
00:34:50,088 --> 00:34:51,089
What?

650
00:34:52,340 --> 00:34:54,675
You don't have to send them food.

651
00:34:55,176 --> 00:34:58,012
Let's keep the good food to ourselves.

652
00:34:58,096 --> 00:35:00,848
Why cook for them?
It's extra work for you.

653
00:35:00,932 --> 00:35:04,018
I made a little extra while I was at it.

654
00:35:04,102 --> 00:35:06,771
Cooking a bit more food
doesn't wear my hands or feet.

655
00:35:06,854 --> 00:35:09,065
Just don't send them anything.

656
00:35:10,024 --> 00:35:12,401
Why would you keep sending them stuff?

657
00:35:12,485 --> 00:35:13,569
MERI

658
00:35:15,113 --> 00:35:16,197
What's up with you?

659
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:18,407
[gasps] Do they not like my food?

660
00:35:19,242 --> 00:35:22,328
No, it's not that.

661
00:35:22,411 --> 00:35:24,872
There's nothing else I can do for them.

662
00:35:24,956 --> 00:35:27,375
I want to do what I can for you and them.

663
00:35:28,543 --> 00:35:30,962
I can only do this while I'm still able.

664
00:35:31,045 --> 00:35:32,213
I don't have much longer.

665
00:35:33,214 --> 00:35:37,093
My shoulders are beginning
to ache, you know.

666
00:35:37,260 --> 00:35:38,678
- [chuckles]
- Mom.

667
00:35:41,848 --> 00:35:43,099
I'm sorry.

668
00:35:43,182 --> 00:35:44,350
What the heck?

669
00:35:44,892 --> 00:35:49,105
Have you finally grown up
now that it's time to get married?

670
00:35:49,272 --> 00:35:51,190
[chuckling]

671
00:35:51,274 --> 00:35:52,275
Meri.

672
00:35:52,775 --> 00:35:56,028
Don't think too much and go to bed.

673
00:35:57,071 --> 00:35:59,532
I have to watch my favorite show. Bye.

674
00:36:00,408 --> 00:36:01,409
Okay, bye.

675
00:36:01,492 --> 00:36:02,660
[line disconnects]

676
00:36:03,703 --> 00:36:05,204
[sighs, sniffles]

677
00:36:08,958 --> 00:36:09,959
[sniffles]

678
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:13,171
[sniffles]

679
00:36:17,675 --> 00:36:19,177
CHEONGHUN 1-GA

680
00:36:19,260 --> 00:36:20,928
[automated voice] You went off course.

681
00:36:21,012 --> 00:36:23,055
- What?
- Rerouting.

682
00:36:24,056 --> 00:36:25,433
Oh, geez.

683
00:36:25,933 --> 00:36:28,811
Turn right at the next corner.

684
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:35,610
[♪ Soft, gripping music playing]

685
00:36:43,034 --> 00:36:44,619
WOOJU

686
00:36:44,702 --> 00:36:45,995
[line ringing]

687
00:36:46,871 --> 00:36:48,664
Kim Wooju, you punk.

688
00:36:53,794 --> 00:36:57,048
Why did it send me this way?

689
00:37:03,721 --> 00:37:04,722
My goodness...

690
00:37:04,805 --> 00:37:07,683
Go straight for 150 meters and turn right.

691
00:37:13,022 --> 00:37:14,357
[tires screech]

692
00:37:18,945 --> 00:37:19,946
What was that?

693
00:37:25,409 --> 00:37:26,577
[gasps]

694
00:37:27,036 --> 00:37:28,246
Are you all right?

695
00:37:28,329 --> 00:37:29,497
[softly exclaims in pain]

696
00:37:30,581 --> 00:37:31,707
[sighing in exhaustion]

697
00:37:34,627 --> 00:37:36,254
[slurring] I'm fine.

698
00:37:37,797 --> 00:37:39,006
Are you really fine?

699
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:41,842
I'm fine. It hurts a bit, but I'm okay.

700
00:37:41,926 --> 00:37:43,803
Let's go to a hospital just in case.

701
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:46,097
I'm good.

702
00:37:47,598 --> 00:37:49,350
I'll give you my number, then.

703
00:37:49,433 --> 00:37:50,768
See a doctor, then call me.

704
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:53,813
What a hassle.

705
00:38:06,409 --> 00:38:07,493
Here you go.

706
00:38:07,576 --> 00:38:08,911
Thank you.

707
00:38:09,412 --> 00:38:11,038
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

708
00:38:20,298 --> 00:38:21,632
KIM WOOJU

709
00:38:22,174 --> 00:38:23,551
"Kim Wooju"?

710
00:38:23,634 --> 00:38:25,011
[♪ Gripping music playing]

711
00:38:36,731 --> 00:38:39,317
Yes, that's my name.

712
00:38:47,366 --> 00:38:48,701
You piece of dirt.

713
00:38:48,784 --> 00:38:49,910
[Kim Wooju groans]

714
00:38:50,369 --> 00:38:52,163
Why did you ignore my calls?

715
00:38:52,872 --> 00:38:54,165
- Me?
- [sighs]

716
00:38:54,415 --> 00:38:55,541
You punk!

717
00:38:55,624 --> 00:38:57,918
Do you think avoiding me will work?

718
00:38:59,045 --> 00:39:01,172
Why would I avoid you? I'm not like that.

719
00:39:01,255 --> 00:39:02,548
[chortles]

720
00:39:06,719 --> 00:39:07,720
You're not?

721
00:39:09,555 --> 00:39:10,723
Take responsibility, then.

722
00:39:10,806 --> 00:39:12,099
"Take responsibility?"

723
00:39:12,183 --> 00:39:13,184
Aah!

724
00:39:14,185 --> 00:39:15,311
You want a settlement?

725
00:39:15,394 --> 00:39:17,813
Whatever. Hand it over right now.

726
00:39:17,897 --> 00:39:18,981
Fine.

727
00:39:19,065 --> 00:39:20,608
How much do you want?

728
00:39:21,609 --> 00:39:22,610
A hundred million won.

729
00:39:23,486 --> 00:39:25,988
- A hundred million won?
- Yes, that's right.

730
00:39:26,322 --> 00:39:28,407
What is wrong with you?

731
00:39:28,491 --> 00:39:29,742
Do you take me for a pushover?

732
00:39:29,825 --> 00:39:31,425
- You're being unreasonable.
- [exclaims]

733
00:39:31,827 --> 00:39:33,120
You're the unreasonable one.

734
00:39:33,204 --> 00:39:34,372
Do as I say.

735
00:39:34,455 --> 00:39:35,581
- Hand it over.
- What?

736
00:39:35,664 --> 00:39:37,208
It's my mom's money.

737
00:39:37,291 --> 00:39:39,460
Hand it over, punk.

738
00:39:39,543 --> 00:39:40,544
You're insane.

739
00:39:44,256 --> 00:39:47,093
Why are you asking me
for the money to give to your mom?

740
00:39:48,219 --> 00:39:49,595
[cat yowls]

741
00:39:49,678 --> 00:39:51,013
Where do you think you're going?

742
00:39:54,100 --> 00:39:55,142
Where are you going?

743
00:39:56,685 --> 00:39:58,270
What do you think you're doing?

744
00:39:59,146 --> 00:40:00,940
Get out of my car.

745
00:40:01,399 --> 00:40:02,525
I won't.

746
00:40:02,608 --> 00:40:04,068
[whines]

747
00:40:05,653 --> 00:40:06,904
[Kim Wooju struggling]

748
00:40:07,696 --> 00:40:08,948
What the...

749
00:40:10,032 --> 00:40:11,534
Drive on.

750
00:40:11,617 --> 00:40:12,785
My goodness.

751
00:40:21,168 --> 00:40:23,212
Why are you so strong?

752
00:40:24,588 --> 00:40:25,673
- Get out.
- No.

753
00:40:25,923 --> 00:40:27,007
[exclaiming]

754
00:40:27,716 --> 00:40:28,843
Get out. [Grunts]

755
00:40:31,637 --> 00:40:32,930
Come here.

756
00:40:33,681 --> 00:40:35,808
- Will you stop it?
- Get out already.

757
00:40:35,891 --> 00:40:37,184
Leave me alone.

758
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:38,519
- Stop it.
- [car horn blares]

759
00:40:39,395 --> 00:40:40,479
Darn you.

760
00:40:43,399 --> 00:40:44,942
[panting]

761
00:40:50,406 --> 00:40:53,325
If you don't stop this, I'll call the police.

762
00:40:56,912 --> 00:40:58,038
Hey, you.

763
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:02,334
[grunts]

764
00:41:04,003 --> 00:41:05,230
[♪ Dramatic guitar music playing]

765
00:41:05,254 --> 00:41:07,173
What are you doing now?

766
00:41:07,256 --> 00:41:08,424
You can't go.

767
00:41:09,383 --> 00:41:11,844
Why do you keep trying to get away?

768
00:41:15,139 --> 00:41:16,932
- Is she crazy?
- Shouldn't we stop her?

769
00:41:17,016 --> 00:41:18,100
You want to run away?

770
00:41:18,184 --> 00:41:19,602
Hey, are you seeing this?

771
00:41:19,685 --> 00:41:20,686
Should we do something?

772
00:41:20,769 --> 00:41:22,329
- What's wrong with her?
- I don't know.

773
00:41:23,522 --> 00:41:24,648
[grunting]

774
00:41:31,238 --> 00:41:32,615
[both panting]

775
00:41:35,993 --> 00:41:37,161
[Meri] Hey.

776
00:41:38,579 --> 00:41:41,040
Aren't you being too hard on me?

777
00:41:41,624 --> 00:41:42,833
[sniffles]

778
00:41:43,751 --> 00:41:46,670
[breath trembling] You cheated on me.

779
00:41:47,463 --> 00:41:50,341
What makes you think you're in the right?

780
00:41:50,424 --> 00:41:54,011
- What?
- Why are you doing this to me?

781
00:41:54,678 --> 00:41:57,973
[crying] Why are you making me do this?

782
00:41:59,683 --> 00:42:01,810
I became a divorcée

783
00:42:02,811 --> 00:42:04,531
without ever getting
to walk down the aisle.

784
00:42:05,981 --> 00:42:07,691
My mom...

785
00:42:07,775 --> 00:42:10,277
It will break her poor heart.

786
00:42:11,529 --> 00:42:13,989
What about my mom?

787
00:42:14,406 --> 00:42:18,702
I can't tell her the truth.
[continues crying]

788
00:42:19,036 --> 00:42:20,356
[♪ Soft melancholy music playing]

789
00:42:20,412 --> 00:42:21,664
[Meri sobbing]

790
00:42:22,831 --> 00:42:25,167
Mom...

791
00:42:26,877 --> 00:42:31,090
[voice shaking] Mom, what should I do?

792
00:42:31,882 --> 00:42:33,884
Mom... [continues sobbing]

793
00:42:34,927 --> 00:42:36,345
Hey, are you all right?

794
00:42:37,763 --> 00:42:38,764
You.

795
00:42:39,431 --> 00:42:40,933
I don't think you are.

796
00:42:41,016 --> 00:42:42,226
[sniffles]

797
00:42:43,519 --> 00:42:44,562
You're...

798
00:42:49,817 --> 00:42:51,318
[♪ dramatic sting]

799
00:42:57,199 --> 00:42:58,492
[crying hysterically]

800
00:43:04,957 --> 00:43:07,501
- It hurts!
- You...

801
00:43:10,504 --> 00:43:11,505
Come here.

802
00:43:12,548 --> 00:43:14,883
Help me.

803
00:43:14,967 --> 00:43:16,343
Why would you

804
00:43:33,694 --> 00:43:35,362
[groans]
- [doctor] How many did we get?

805
00:43:35,446 --> 00:43:37,072
[nurse] A total of 17.

806
00:43:37,156 --> 00:43:38,407
[doctor] Did we get everything?

807
00:43:38,490 --> 00:43:39,700
There's one more over there.

808
00:43:39,701 --> 00:43:59,768
Officail Website : kissasian.be

809
00:43:59,792 --> 00:44:19,858
Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

810
00:43:39,783 --> 00:43:41,076
Oh, here it is.

811
00:43:47,333 --> 00:43:49,084
[surgical instruments clatter]

812
00:43:50,377 --> 00:43:52,338
We're done.

813
00:43:53,339 --> 00:43:55,299
Don't shower for the next two days.

814
00:43:55,382 --> 00:43:57,426
I'll prescribe you
a painkiller and antibiotics.

815
00:43:57,509 --> 00:43:59,053
Okay. [Sniffles]

816
00:43:59,553 --> 00:44:00,971
[sighs wearily]

817
00:44:01,472 --> 00:44:03,140
Hey, how did it happen?

818
00:44:03,223 --> 00:44:04,642
Wasn't she drunk?

819
00:44:04,725 --> 00:44:07,061
She reeked of alcohol.

820
00:44:07,519 --> 00:44:09,521
How could you confuse

821
00:44:09,605 --> 00:44:11,325
a cactus for a stool
because you were drunk?

822
00:44:11,398 --> 00:44:14,193
Sitting on a cactus must be so painful.

823
00:44:15,903 --> 00:44:17,780
[♪ Comical music playing]

824
00:44:39,760 --> 00:44:42,888
[doctor] It'll throb for a few days,
but she'll be fine.

825
00:44:44,098 --> 00:44:46,558
It's usually a job for the interns,

826
00:44:46,642 --> 00:44:48,769
but I did it myself because you asked.

827
00:44:48,852 --> 00:44:51,146
[chuckles] Thanks, Jingyeong.

828
00:44:51,647 --> 00:44:54,191
- You were the first to come to mind.
- What?

829
00:44:54,274 --> 00:44:55,943
Only when you need help?

830
00:44:56,026 --> 00:44:58,237
You've been back for a month,
and you never called.

831
00:44:59,405 --> 00:45:00,531
How did you know I was back?

832
00:45:00,614 --> 00:45:03,575
My dad is your grandmother's doctor.

833
00:45:04,368 --> 00:45:05,953
He heard it during her checkup.

834
00:45:06,036 --> 00:45:07,246
Aah!

835
00:45:07,329 --> 00:45:08,622
So...

836
00:45:09,248 --> 00:45:11,417
Who is that woman?

837
00:45:11,500 --> 00:45:12,543
Your girlfriend?

838
00:45:12,626 --> 00:45:13,961
It didn't seem so.

839
00:45:14,044 --> 00:45:15,045
My girlfriend?

840
00:45:15,546 --> 00:45:17,005
As if she'd be my girlfriend.

841
00:45:17,798 --> 00:45:20,092
She's just some drunk I met in the street.

842
00:45:20,175 --> 00:45:21,468
She bumped into my car.

843
00:45:23,011 --> 00:45:25,347
You did that to her?

844
00:45:25,806 --> 00:45:27,683
What? Well, no.

845
00:45:28,684 --> 00:45:30,185
It's a long story.

846
00:45:30,269 --> 00:45:31,520
I'll tell you another time.

847
00:45:32,271 --> 00:45:35,149
Do you work late all the time?

848
00:45:35,816 --> 00:45:38,110
Yes, I'm preparing for a conference,

849
00:45:38,193 --> 00:45:40,112
so I have to stay up for a whole week.

850
00:45:40,487 --> 00:45:41,655
[yawns]

851
00:45:43,449 --> 00:45:44,658
[yawning] I'm so tired.

852
00:45:47,286 --> 00:45:49,413
Cover your mouth when you yawn. [Scoffs]

853
00:45:55,210 --> 00:45:56,295
Wooju.

854
00:45:57,963 --> 00:46:00,257
I treated her, so you owe me a coffee.

855
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:01,341
A coffee?

856
00:46:01,800 --> 00:46:02,843
Sounds good.

857
00:46:07,848 --> 00:46:09,850
What's wrong with her?

858
00:46:09,933 --> 00:46:11,435
I told her to get an X-ray.

859
00:46:13,979 --> 00:46:15,355
Hey, Jingyeong.

860
00:46:15,439 --> 00:46:16,774
The coffee has to wait.

861
00:46:17,399 --> 00:46:18,650
Wooju.

862
00:46:19,318 --> 00:46:20,861
Kim Wooju!

863
00:46:23,447 --> 00:46:25,365
Couldn't he even stay for a coffee?

864
00:46:31,830 --> 00:46:32,915
[yawns]

865
00:46:37,461 --> 00:46:40,005
[clears throat] I could take a taxi.

866
00:46:41,715 --> 00:46:42,716
And sit like that?

867
00:46:43,717 --> 00:46:44,843
[chuckles softly]

868
00:46:46,804 --> 00:46:49,181
You must've been so flustered earlier.

869
00:46:49,264 --> 00:46:51,892
The alcohol must've made me lose my mind.

870
00:46:53,060 --> 00:46:55,646
I know you thought I was a weirdo.

871
00:46:57,189 --> 00:47:00,859
To be honest, I had a bad day today.

872
00:47:00,943 --> 00:47:04,029
I can't go into detail
since we just met, but.

873
00:47:05,239 --> 00:47:06,824
I mistook you for someone else.

874
00:47:06,907 --> 00:47:09,117
You happened to have the same name.

875
00:47:13,372 --> 00:47:17,835
By the way,
I don't need to get an arm X-ray.

876
00:47:19,127 --> 00:47:21,380
- It was just a slight bump...
- [sunroof whirring]

877
00:47:22,339 --> 00:47:23,590
[Kim Wooju exhales]

878
00:47:24,842 --> 00:47:28,011
I smell the alcohol whenever you talk.

879
00:47:28,971 --> 00:47:30,013
I feel dizzy.

880
00:47:30,264 --> 00:47:32,057
[♪ Whimsical music playing]

881
00:47:44,820 --> 00:47:46,071
Excuse me. [Clears throat]

882
00:47:46,154 --> 00:47:47,281
I'm really sorry,

883
00:47:47,823 --> 00:47:48,991
but could you pull over?

884
00:47:50,450 --> 00:47:51,451
What for?

885
00:47:51,535 --> 00:47:53,620
Going backwards gives me motion sickness.

886
00:47:53,704 --> 00:47:55,581
Seriously?

887
00:47:57,332 --> 00:47:58,625
Fine.

888
00:47:58,709 --> 00:47:59,710
Thank you.

889
00:48:29,489 --> 00:48:30,782
[exhales]

890
00:48:30,866 --> 00:48:31,992
Are you all right?

891
00:48:36,038 --> 00:48:37,205
[groans softly]

892
00:48:42,210 --> 00:48:43,378
[sighs]

893
00:48:47,841 --> 00:48:49,176
[♪ Slow poignant music playing]

894
00:48:49,676 --> 00:48:50,969
[Meri sighs]

895
00:48:56,058 --> 00:48:57,851
The sun is rising.

896
00:49:01,939 --> 00:49:04,441
It's like a red flower

897
00:49:06,944 --> 00:49:09,237
blooming through the dark.

898
00:49:10,614 --> 00:49:11,990
[Meri sighs]

899
00:49:13,617 --> 00:49:16,078
Even though my world crumbles,

900
00:49:16,995 --> 00:49:18,455
the sun still rises,

901
00:49:19,539 --> 00:49:21,833
and morning still comes.

902
00:49:26,672 --> 00:49:29,341
There's always a way out, right?

903
00:49:33,303 --> 00:49:36,807
It feels as if Mother Nature

904
00:49:38,767 --> 00:49:41,269
is giving me a message.

905
00:49:41,353 --> 00:49:43,063
[stomach rumbling]

906
00:49:44,856 --> 00:49:46,024
[chuckles softly]

907
00:49:48,527 --> 00:49:50,320
The message must be "feed me."

908
00:49:51,279 --> 00:49:52,739
[♪ Whimsical music playing]

909
00:49:52,823 --> 00:49:54,282
[stomach continues rumbling]

910
00:49:56,368 --> 00:49:58,328
I'm the type... [clears throat]

911
00:50:00,497 --> 00:50:03,375
Who must eat breakfast every morning.

912
00:50:04,876 --> 00:50:06,753
Would you like to get breakfast?

913
00:50:06,837 --> 00:50:08,005
It'll be my treat.

914
00:50:08,088 --> 00:50:10,048
I know a good hangover soup place nearby.

915
00:50:10,132 --> 00:50:11,466
No, thanks.

916
00:50:12,009 --> 00:50:13,010
Let's go.

917
00:50:13,093 --> 00:50:14,386
Okay.

918
00:50:42,080 --> 00:50:43,290
[grunts]

919
00:50:49,921 --> 00:50:51,548
Thank you.

920
00:50:53,175 --> 00:50:54,384
[car door closes]

921
00:50:55,677 --> 00:50:57,304
About your arm.

922
00:50:58,597 --> 00:51:01,099
You should get it checked.

923
00:51:01,183 --> 00:51:02,383
Don't complain about it later.

924
00:51:02,851 --> 00:51:03,852
Okay.

925
00:51:04,311 --> 00:51:06,438
Thanks so much for everything today.

926
00:51:06,938 --> 00:51:09,566
Text me your account details.
I'll wire you the gas...

927
00:51:18,784 --> 00:51:20,160
[♪ whimsical music playing]

928
00:51:29,169 --> 00:51:30,295
[sighs]

929
00:51:30,378 --> 00:51:32,589
What is wrong with me?

930
00:51:35,133 --> 00:51:36,468
Oh, whatever.

931
00:51:37,052 --> 00:51:38,637
[groans]

932
00:51:40,847 --> 00:51:42,390
It hurts.

933
00:51:46,019 --> 00:51:47,395
[sighs in exasperation]

934
00:51:49,231 --> 00:51:50,500
[♪ Triumphant music playing on video]

935
00:51:50,524 --> 00:51:54,402
[presenter over video] Where every step
and every breath carries elegance.

936
00:51:55,237 --> 00:51:57,030
Where life becomes art.

937
00:51:57,114 --> 00:51:58,698
[audience clapping]

938
00:51:59,324 --> 00:52:01,201
It's Beauté Palace.

939
00:52:02,577 --> 00:52:04,222
[employee 1] Beauté Department Store's
wedding festival

940
00:52:04,246 --> 00:52:06,248
is for newlyweds
who want a great beginning.

941
00:52:06,331 --> 00:52:08,834
A Beauté Palace unit
worth five million dollars

942
00:52:08,917 --> 00:52:11,169
you just saw in the video
is the grand prize.

943
00:52:11,253 --> 00:52:12,295
Yes, that's right.

944
00:52:12,379 --> 00:52:14,339
It's Beauté Construction's
ambitious new project,

945
00:52:14,422 --> 00:52:16,967
a high-end luxury town house.

946
00:52:17,050 --> 00:52:20,554
It gathered a lot of attention,
and so many entered the raffle.

947
00:52:20,637 --> 00:52:23,974
The couple that wins the apartment
must be so pleased.

948
00:52:24,057 --> 00:52:26,601
I'd have delayed my wedding
if only I'd known.

949
00:52:26,685 --> 00:52:28,645
I'm so sad I'm not a newlywed!

950
00:52:28,770 --> 00:52:30,230
[all chuckle]

951
00:52:30,313 --> 00:52:32,357
- Shall we pick the winners?
- Yes.

952
00:52:37,279 --> 00:52:39,739
Everyone wants one of these at home.

953
00:52:39,823 --> 00:52:42,534
A must-have
for the fashion-conscious, a styler!

954
00:52:43,493 --> 00:52:45,829
Why make a huge fuss when it's rigged?

955
00:52:46,746 --> 00:52:48,790
It must look real to avoid complaints.

956
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,001
You think?

957
00:52:52,502 --> 00:52:54,087
I'm sure you took care of it.

958
00:52:54,171 --> 00:52:55,565
[employee 2 over TV] Congratulations.

959
00:52:55,589 --> 00:52:56,715
What do I do now?

960
00:52:57,382 --> 00:52:58,592
[employee 2] One, zero,

961
00:52:59,634 --> 00:53:01,678
seven, three!

962
00:53:01,761 --> 00:53:03,889
Ha Minyeong, congratulations!

963
00:53:03,972 --> 00:53:05,682
LEE SEONGGYU
DATE ENTERED: APRIL 12

964
00:53:05,765 --> 00:53:06,975
Lee Seonggyu.

965
00:53:07,726 --> 00:53:08,852
The mayor's wife's nephew?

966
00:53:08,935 --> 00:53:10,520
Yes, that's right.

967
00:53:10,604 --> 00:53:12,355
[♪ Enthralling music playing]

968
00:53:24,492 --> 00:53:25,660
[taps hand]

969
00:53:25,911 --> 00:53:26,912
In case I get mixed up.

970
00:53:26,995 --> 00:53:28,538
[audience clapping]

971
00:53:30,916 --> 00:53:34,211
Beauté Department Store's
30th anniversary wedding festival.

972
00:53:34,294 --> 00:53:38,256
It's time to select
the winner of the grand prize.

973
00:53:38,340 --> 00:53:41,218
Let's not waste time and get right to it.

974
00:53:41,301 --> 00:53:45,764
Beauté Department Store's CEO
will select the grand prize winner.

975
00:53:45,847 --> 00:53:47,224
Sir! Come on up.

976
00:53:50,518 --> 00:53:52,729
[audience cheering, clapping]

977
00:54:00,570 --> 00:54:01,696
[all chuckle]

978
00:54:03,031 --> 00:54:04,699
[♪ Gripping music playing]

979
00:54:27,681 --> 00:54:30,809
[employee 1] Our CEO is doing his best
to select the right winner.

980
00:54:33,186 --> 00:54:34,396
Give him some applause!

981
00:54:34,479 --> 00:54:35,772
[all cheering]

982
00:54:52,580 --> 00:54:53,832
He picked a ticket at last.

983
00:54:54,624 --> 00:54:57,168
The grand prize,
the Beauté Palace unit goes to...

984
00:54:57,627 --> 00:54:58,707
Please announce the winner.

985
00:55:00,297 --> 00:55:04,843
As the CEO of Beauté Department Store,
I will announce the winner myself.

986
00:55:05,760 --> 00:55:06,880
The grand prize winner is...

987
00:55:08,555 --> 00:55:09,806
[drum roll]

988
00:55:13,226 --> 00:55:14,436
[♪ Dramatic sting]

989
00:55:19,899 --> 00:55:21,192
[vibrating]

990
00:55:30,368 --> 00:55:31,828
[phone continues vibrating]

991
00:55:41,379 --> 00:55:42,589
Hello?

992
00:55:43,631 --> 00:55:44,674
Is this Ms. Yoo Meri?

993
00:55:44,758 --> 00:55:47,177
This is Beauté Department Store's PR Team.

994
00:55:50,180 --> 00:55:51,264
A raffle?

995
00:55:52,891 --> 00:55:55,143
[grunts] What raffle do you mean?

996
00:55:55,226 --> 00:55:58,271
2 MONTHS AGO

997
00:55:58,563 --> 00:55:59,564
[Meri grunts]

998
00:55:59,898 --> 00:56:01,274
Sorry.

999
00:56:06,654 --> 00:56:07,840
WIN A TOWNHOUSE WORTH FIVE MILLION!

1000
00:56:07,864 --> 00:56:09,282
[♪ Upbeat whimsical music playing]

1001
00:56:11,409 --> 00:56:12,649
YOO MERI DATE ENTERED: APRIL 15

1002
00:56:13,620 --> 00:56:16,623
If I win, I'll spend the rest of my life...

1003
00:56:17,457 --> 00:56:20,377
No, I'll do good even in the afterlife.

1004
00:56:37,060 --> 00:56:38,478
Oh, that.

1005
00:56:39,854 --> 00:56:41,398
I won?

1006
00:56:42,524 --> 00:56:43,525
What?

1007
00:56:44,401 --> 00:56:45,610
Yes.

1008
00:56:45,693 --> 00:56:48,154
Yes, that's me. I'm Yoo Meri.

1009
00:56:49,239 --> 00:56:51,074
Yes, of course. I'm sure it's me.

1010
00:56:51,157 --> 00:56:53,159
Congratulations, Ms. Yoo.

1011
00:56:53,243 --> 00:56:54,994
I need to confirm your identity.

1012
00:56:55,078 --> 00:56:57,288
Can you send us a few documents?

1013
00:56:58,123 --> 00:56:59,165
Oh, documents.

1014
00:56:59,249 --> 00:57:00,834
Yes, of course, I'll send them.

1015
00:57:00,917 --> 00:57:02,293
Give me a moment.

1016
00:57:07,757 --> 00:57:08,967
Yes, I'm ready.

1017
00:57:09,050 --> 00:57:10,490
[employee 1] A copy of your ID card.

1018
00:57:10,552 --> 00:57:12,011
A copy of my ID.

1019
00:57:12,929 --> 00:57:14,209
Proof that you don't own a home.

1020
00:57:14,431 --> 00:57:16,933
Proof that I don't own a home.

1021
00:57:18,101 --> 00:57:19,477
[employee 1] Proof of income,

1022
00:57:19,561 --> 00:57:21,646
and proof of marriage. That's it.

1023
00:57:21,729 --> 00:57:23,189
Proof of...

1024
00:57:23,273 --> 00:57:25,233
- Proof of marriage?
- Yes.

1025
00:57:25,316 --> 00:57:28,361
To be eligible to win, you must make
less than 80 million won a year

1026
00:57:28,445 --> 00:57:30,488
and be newlyweds who don't own a home.

1027
00:57:31,948 --> 00:57:34,325
Yes, okay. I understand.

1028
00:57:34,826 --> 00:57:35,827
Bye.

1029
00:57:40,915 --> 00:57:42,208
Proof of marriage?

1030
00:57:44,419 --> 00:57:45,628
Will they cancel my win

1031
00:57:46,629 --> 00:57:48,423
if I say I'm divorced?

1032
00:57:51,092 --> 00:57:52,260
[phone chimes]

1033
00:57:53,303 --> 00:57:54,423
I didn't hand that thing in.

1034
00:57:54,471 --> 00:57:56,097
[♪ Upbeat music playing]

1035
00:58:02,562 --> 00:58:03,813
SEOUL FAMILY COURT

1036
00:58:06,649 --> 00:58:08,109
DIVORCE DECREE

1037
00:58:08,193 --> 00:58:09,360
I still have it.

1038
00:58:15,575 --> 00:58:17,702
Since I haven't handed it in yet...

1039
00:58:18,077 --> 00:58:19,287
FAMILY REGISTRATION DETAILS

1040
00:58:21,539 --> 00:58:22,790
SPOUSE: KIM WOOJU

1041
00:58:26,211 --> 00:58:27,712
I'm still legally married.

1042
00:58:31,633 --> 00:58:32,818
THIS DOCUMENT CERTIFIES THE ABOVE DETAILS

1043
00:58:32,842 --> 00:58:33,968
[gasps]

1044
00:58:44,312 --> 00:58:46,397
I checked everything thoroughly.

1045
00:58:47,065 --> 00:58:49,400
They're newlyweds
who got married five months ago,

1046
00:58:49,484 --> 00:58:50,693
don't own a home,

1047
00:58:50,777 --> 00:58:52,417
and their income meets the criteria, too.

1048
00:58:52,445 --> 00:58:54,739
She meets every requirement completely.

1049
00:58:57,450 --> 00:59:00,119
Shall we go ahead with the award ceremony?

1050
00:59:00,995 --> 00:59:02,539
Our CEO should attend as well.

1051
00:59:02,622 --> 00:59:03,782
- Postpone it for now.
- Okay.

1052
00:59:04,707 --> 00:59:07,001
What? To when?

1053
00:59:07,085 --> 00:59:08,127
[clicks tongue]

1054
00:59:10,213 --> 00:59:13,466
Well, Yoo Meri said
her husband couldn't come.

1055
00:59:13,550 --> 00:59:16,594
If we push back the ceremony,
I need to ask her if they'll be free.

1056
00:59:17,512 --> 00:59:18,680
Her husband can't come?

1057
00:59:20,431 --> 00:59:21,516
Why not?

1058
00:59:21,599 --> 00:59:24,477
I talked to her on the phone earlier.

1059
00:59:25,395 --> 00:59:27,105
Yes, I got all the documents.

1060
00:59:28,273 --> 00:59:31,067
Will your husband be abroad for a while?

1061
00:59:31,150 --> 00:59:32,360
Well.

1062
00:59:33,695 --> 00:59:35,405
I don't see why you can't come alone.

1063
00:59:35,488 --> 00:59:37,657
- That's a no.
- What?

1064
00:59:37,740 --> 00:59:39,534
Didn't you read the fine print?

1065
00:59:39,617 --> 00:59:41,244
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

1066
00:59:42,203 --> 00:59:44,080
The fine print?

1067
00:59:44,163 --> 00:59:48,084
Yes, I just noticed the fine print
of the terms and conditions.

1068
00:59:48,167 --> 00:59:49,294
"The win will be canceled

1069
00:59:49,377 --> 00:59:52,088
if it turns out they lied
on any of the documents,

1070
00:59:52,171 --> 00:59:55,466
and the winner will be held
legally responsible."

1071
00:59:58,803 --> 01:00:00,054
And also...

1072
01:00:01,514 --> 01:00:05,268
"The winner must actively participate in
any company promotions,

1073
01:00:05,351 --> 01:00:08,605
and they must attend
the award ceremony as a couple."

1074
01:00:08,688 --> 01:00:09,772
That's a must.

1075
01:00:09,856 --> 01:00:11,232
There are no exceptions.

1076
01:00:11,733 --> 01:00:12,775
What?

1077
01:00:13,359 --> 01:00:16,279
You said earlier today
that it wouldn't matter.

1078
01:00:16,362 --> 01:00:17,488
Why the sudden change?

1079
01:00:18,740 --> 01:00:21,951
What happens if my husband can't make it?

1080
01:00:25,246 --> 01:00:26,372
Then it will be canceled.

1081
01:00:26,456 --> 01:00:29,125
It'll be canceled? That's not fair.

1082
01:00:29,208 --> 01:00:31,294
I won the raffle. You just need me.

1083
01:00:31,377 --> 01:00:33,212
Who cares if my husband's there or not?

1084
01:00:33,296 --> 01:00:34,422
That's the rule.

1085
01:00:35,131 --> 01:00:36,132
That's the rule.

1086
01:00:36,215 --> 01:00:37,508
There's nothing I can do.

1087
01:00:38,134 --> 01:00:39,218
Ah!

1088
01:00:40,428 --> 01:00:41,429
[sighs]

1089
01:00:41,512 --> 01:00:43,431
CEO YOO MERI

1090
01:00:44,140 --> 01:00:45,642
Okay, I got it for now.

1091
01:00:45,725 --> 01:00:47,769
I'll be in touch.

1092
01:00:52,774 --> 01:00:55,526
What kind of rule is that?

1093
01:00:56,819 --> 01:00:57,987
This is madness.

1094
01:01:00,740 --> 01:01:02,784
[♪ Pop music playing over speakers]

1095
01:01:07,538 --> 01:01:08,539
Give me a kiss.

1096
01:01:10,083 --> 01:01:11,310
- I love you.
- I love you, too.

1097
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:13,086
MERI

1098
01:01:16,547 --> 01:01:18,233
[automated voice] To leave a message,
press one.

1099
01:01:18,257 --> 01:01:21,177
To leave your number, press two.

1100
01:01:22,303 --> 01:01:23,638
- [beep]
- Hello?

1101
01:01:26,641 --> 01:01:29,227
It's me. I can't seem to reach you.

1102
01:01:30,937 --> 01:01:33,898
I have something urgent to discuss.
Can you call me quickly?

1103
01:01:35,650 --> 01:01:37,318
It's really important.

1104
01:01:38,111 --> 01:01:41,364
I won a lucky draw kind of thing.

1105
01:01:41,864 --> 01:01:43,783
[♪ Jazz music playing over speakers]

1106
01:01:43,866 --> 01:01:45,034
[exhales]

1107
01:01:45,576 --> 01:01:46,911
This is paradise.

1108
01:01:49,288 --> 01:01:50,289
Hey, baby.

1109
01:01:51,290 --> 01:01:52,291
You're back.

1110
01:01:53,751 --> 01:01:54,752
My cutie.

1111
01:01:55,420 --> 01:01:56,504
[both giggle]

1112
01:01:57,338 --> 01:01:58,381
Aren't you hungry?

1113
01:01:58,464 --> 01:02:00,299
- Are you hungry, Jenny?
- Yes.

1114
01:02:00,800 --> 01:02:02,427
- Shall we go eat?
- Yes.

1115
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:03,886
[phone vibrates]

1116
01:02:03,970 --> 01:02:05,054
NEW MESSAGE

1117
01:02:07,849 --> 01:02:08,969
YOU HAVE A NEW VOICE MESSAGE

1118
01:02:09,016 --> 01:02:10,184
MERI

1119
01:02:11,519 --> 01:02:12,729
Who is it from?

1120
01:02:14,981 --> 01:02:15,982
It's a spam message.

1121
01:02:18,526 --> 01:02:19,569
[sighs]

1122
01:02:19,652 --> 01:02:20,653
BLOCK CONTACT.

1123
01:02:20,737 --> 01:02:21,863
BLOCK

1124
01:02:23,281 --> 01:02:24,490
Let's go.

1125
01:02:24,574 --> 01:02:25,742
Okay.

1126
01:02:25,743 --> 01:02:45,810
Officail Website : kissasian.be

1127
01:02:45,834 --> 01:03:05,900
Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

1128
01:02:25,825 --> 01:02:28,619
WOOJU

1129
01:02:29,245 --> 01:02:30,455
[line ringing]

1130
01:02:31,205 --> 01:02:32,808
[automated voice]
The call cannot be connected.

1131
01:02:32,832 --> 01:02:34,834
Transferring to voicemail.

1132
01:02:34,917 --> 01:02:36,461
- [line disconnects]
- [exclaims]

1133
01:02:37,044 --> 01:02:40,339
Come on. Pick up.

1134
01:02:42,467 --> 01:02:46,679
I can't do anything if I can't talk to you.

1135
01:02:50,141 --> 01:02:51,893
[♪ Whimsical music playing]

1136
01:02:56,022 --> 01:02:57,565
It's as good as out of my reach.

1137
01:02:58,900 --> 01:03:00,276
It's a pie in the sky.

1138
01:03:03,404 --> 01:03:04,572
[phone vibrates]

1139
01:03:10,411 --> 01:03:11,579
This is Kim Wooju.

1140
01:03:12,205 --> 01:03:14,248
I was wondering if you went to the doctor.

1141
01:03:14,332 --> 01:03:16,959
No, I was too busy to...

1142
01:03:19,462 --> 01:03:21,589
NO, I WAS TOO BUSY TO.

1143
01:03:23,132 --> 01:03:25,301
KIM WOOJU

1144
01:03:25,384 --> 01:03:27,011
[♪ dramatic guitar music playing]

1145
01:03:38,689 --> 01:03:42,527
WHERE LIFE BECOMES ART

1146
01:03:47,824 --> 01:03:49,742
KIM WOOJU

1147
01:03:54,622 --> 01:03:55,957
KIM WOOJU

1148
01:03:56,040 --> 01:03:57,375
He has the same name.

1149
01:03:58,543 --> 01:04:01,629
The department store people
won't know if I bring someone else.

1150
01:04:02,672 --> 01:04:04,006
They've never seen him.

1151
01:04:14,141 --> 01:04:15,981
[♪ Soft orchestral music playing
in background]

1152
01:04:25,403 --> 01:04:26,487
What did the doctor say?

1153
01:04:26,946 --> 01:04:28,066
Did you get a doctor's note?

1154
01:04:28,906 --> 01:04:30,116
Oh, the doctor.

1155
01:04:32,159 --> 01:04:34,036
I was too busy to see one.

1156
01:04:42,336 --> 01:04:43,713
Are you perhaps married?

1157
01:04:45,339 --> 01:04:46,340
I'm sorry?

1158
01:04:47,341 --> 01:04:50,219
Are you a married man?

1159
01:04:51,178 --> 01:04:52,179
No, why?

1160
01:04:52,638 --> 01:04:54,807
[chuckles nervously] That's a relief.

1161
01:04:54,891 --> 01:04:55,892
What is?

1162
01:04:56,851 --> 01:04:59,478
I gave it a lot of thought.

1163
01:05:00,104 --> 01:05:04,483
I know it's rash to say this
when we've only met once,

1164
01:05:05,192 --> 01:05:06,986
but you're the only one I can turn to.

1165
01:05:10,781 --> 01:05:12,533
Could you

1166
01:05:14,410 --> 01:05:15,703
be my husband?

1167
01:05:16,162 --> 01:05:17,997
[♪ Upbeat dreamy music playing]

1168
01:05:24,503 --> 01:05:26,255
[♪ Upbeat pop music playing]

1169
01:06:01,165 --> 01:06:03,834
WOULD YOU MARRY ME?

1170
01:06:03,918 --> 01:06:05,687
[Kim Wooju] You'll pay me
to play your fake husband

1171
01:06:05,711 --> 01:06:07,004
- for a day?
- [Meri] Yes.

1172
01:06:07,088 --> 01:06:10,758
[Kim Wooju] I'm not kind enough
to be generous to a scammer.

1173
01:06:10,841 --> 01:06:12,110
[assistant] The husband must be present.

1174
01:06:12,134 --> 01:06:13,302
Otherwise, we'll redraw.

1175
01:06:13,386 --> 01:06:15,238
- Are they in?
- [Songhee] They'll call after discussing.

1176
01:06:15,262 --> 01:06:17,306
[man] You quit as team leader if you fail.

1177
01:06:17,390 --> 01:06:20,452
[Meri] I lost everything in a rental con,
but I won a five-million-dollar house.

1178
01:06:20,476 --> 01:06:22,853
- I just need a husband to tag along.
- You won a prize?

1179
01:06:22,937 --> 01:06:24,480
So, that's what this is all about.

1180
01:06:24,563 --> 01:06:27,650
Do you have any idea
how risky this scam is?

1181
01:06:27,733 --> 01:06:28,859
It's me. How have you been?

1182
01:06:28,943 --> 01:06:30,069
I'm in Seoul.

1183
01:06:30,152 --> 01:06:31,862
I'm one of the residents here.

1184
01:06:31,946 --> 01:06:34,865
- Over there?
- That one?

1185
01:06:36,951 --> 01:06:38,953
Translated by Jennifer Jean Lim
